197 (d) The registration statement shall be executed under
198 oath as follows:
199 (1) If the registrant is an individual, by him or her.
200 (2) If the registrant is a partnership, by the majority
201 of the members thereof.
202 (3) If the registrant is a person other than an
203 individual or a partnership, by a majority of the officers
204 thereof or persons performing the functions of officers or by
205 a majority of the board of directors thereof or persons
206 performing the functions of directors, if any.
207 (e) A registration statement or supplement required to
208 be filed under this section shall be filed in electronic form,
209 in addition to any other form that may be required by the
210 Secretary of State.
211 Section 4. (a) No later than December 31 annually, each
212 foreign supported political organization operating within the
213 state shall register with the Secretary of State and provide
214 all of the following information:
215 (1) The name of the foreign supported political
216 organization, its business address, and the names, titles, and
217 addresses of all officers and directors of the foreign
218 supported political organization.
219 (2) If the foreign supported political organization is
220 affiliated with or a chapter of a national organization, the
221 name of the national organization, its address, and the names
222 and addresses of its officers and directors.
223 (3) A detailed statement of the money and other things
224 of value spent or disposed of by the foreign supported
Page 8

of value spent or disposed of by the foreign supported
HB358 INTRODUCED
225 political organization during the preceding calendar year in
226 furtherance of or in connection with activities to influence
227 any agency or public official, local government entity, or the
228 public within the State of Alabama, including, but not limited
229 to, activities related to formulating, adopting, or changing
230 the policies or laws of this state or electing a candidate to
231 local or state public office.
232 (4) A detailed statement of any expenditures of money
233 or other things of value made by the foreign supported
234 political organization within the prior calendar year.
235 (5) A detailed statement of all money or other things
236 of value received by the foreign supported political
237 organization from a hostile foreign principal or an agent of a
238 hostile foreign principal during the preceding calendar year.
239 (b) A registered foreign supported organization shall
240 update the information required by subsection (a) with the
241 Secretary of State every 90 days.
242 Section 5. Upon receipt of a complaint that an agent of
243 a hostile foreign principal or a foreign supported political
244 organization has failed to comply with the registration and
245 reporting requirements of this act, or upon its own
246 determination, the Secretary of State shall investigate, and
247 upon finding a violation, impose civil penalties of up to ten
248 thousand dollars ($10,000) for failure to timely file a
249 statement required by this act.
250 If the Secretary of State finds that a violation was
251 willful or a repeat violation of this act, the civil penalties
252 shall be not less than ten thousand dollars ($10,000) nor more
Page 9

shall be not less than ten thousand dollars ($10,000) nor more
HB358 INTRODUCED
253 than two hundred thousand dollars ($200,000) per such
254 violation.
255 Section 6. (a) Any person upon whom a civil penalty has
256 been imposed pursuant to Section 5 may seek a review of the
257 penalty by filing a written notice with the Secretary of State
258 no later than 21 days after the date on which notification of
259 the imposition of the penalty was sent. The Secretary of State
260 shall refer the review to the State Ethics Commission.
261 (b) The commission may set aside or reduce a civil
262 penalty upon a showing of good cause. The person seeking
263 review shall bear the burden of proof.
264 Section 7. This act shall become effective on October
265 1, 2026.
